7.1.1 - W11SR08: Ineffective SIAM Integration and Access Governance
ISM controls:
•	1173; 1504; 1505 (Relating to the management of user access requests and authorisations).
•	0421; 0422 (Relating to the use of automated mechanisms to support user account management).
•	0582; 0800 (Relating to the regular review of access permissions and system privileges).
Current Risk
The lack of effective Service Integration and Management (SIAM) processes and procedures—specifically concerning automated access request workflows within Ivanti Neurons—presents a significant security gap. Without robust, automated approval and actioning cycles, there is a risk of unauthorised or misconfigured system and user access being granted, leading to a compromise of the confidentiality, integrity, or availability of departmental systems and data.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
LIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	HIGH
Recommendations:
•	Formalise SIAM Access Workflows: Develop and document end-to-end SIAM procedures that define clear ownership and approval authorities for all Windows 11 and Microsoft 365 access requests.
•	Integrate Ivanti Neurons with Identity Providers: Fully automate the provisioning and de-provisioning of accounts by integrating Ivanti Neurons with Entra ID (Azure AD), ensuring access is automatically revoked when a user’s status changes.
•	Implement Just-In-Time (JIT) Access: Utilise automated workflows to provide time-bound, elevated access where required, reducing the persistence of high-privileged accounts across the management plane.
- Treatment #1
•	Configure Ivanti Neurons to mandate multi-stage approvals for high-risk access requests, ensuring a clear audit trail is maintained for every authorisation.
•	Perform monthly automated reconciliation between the SIAM request logs and the actual active accounts in Entra ID/Intune to identify and remediate "ghost" accounts or privilege creep.
•	Implement automated alerting for any access changes that bypass the formal SIAM process, enabling rapid response by the security operations team.
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
The transition from manual or ad-hoc access management to a formalised, automated SIAM model significantly reduces the window of opportunity for unauthorised access. By ensuring all access is approved, logged, and automatically provisioned/de-provisioned, the likelihood of a compromise due to access misconfiguration is lowered to "Unlikely."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
UNLIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	MEDIUM

